When investigating a suspected duplicate content section, **check whether the second "section" is actually an empty component** with no visible content rather than a true content duplicate.

The CTA banner section (`cta-banner`) is the most common culprit — it renders a `style="padding:2rem 1rem;background:#F5F5F0"` container shell even when the content data resolves to `null` or empty.

**Fix:** Add a null-guard in the section dispatch or the component itself:

```tsx
// In the dispatch loop ([[...slug]].tsx):
{sections.map((section, idx) => {
  const Component = SECTION_MAP[section.id]
  const sectionData = resolveContent(content, section.content)
  if (!sectionData || Object.keys(sectionData).length === 0) return null
  // ... render
})}
```

For reference material on this debugging path, see `references/ssr-content-duplication-debugging.md`.

## Troubleshooting Checklist"}
